---
import { Layout } from "/layouts/layout.squirrel";
const title = "Learn about layouts";
---
<Layout>
    <h1>${title}</h1>

    <p>Layout are the same like pages, but they are define the layout of a page</p>

    <div style="margin-right: 2rem; width: 300px; color: black;">
        <div style="border:1px dashed white; margin-bottom:2px; padding:2px; background-color: rgba(231,232,233,0.7)"><center>HEADER</center></div>
        <div style="border:1px dashed white; height: 7rem; display: flex; align-items: center;
  justify-content: center; background-color: rgba(22,23,24,0.9); color: white;"><div>HOLE</div></div>
        <div style="border:1px dashed white; margin-top:2px; padding:2px; background-color: rgba(231,232,233,0.7)"><center>FOOTER</center></div>
    </div>

    <h4 class="mt-2">Layout example</h4>

        You define a layout with have a slot.
        A slot if a hole where they page that use the layout fill the content in.

        <pre class="code" data-lang="Squirrel"><code>---
import { Header } from "/components/header.squirrel";
import { Footer } from "/components/footer.squirrel";
---
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8" />
        <link href="http://foo.com/css" rel="stylesheet" />
    </head>
    <body>
        <Navbar />
        <slot/>
        <Footer />
    </body>
</html>
</code></pre>

<h4>Use layout on a page</h4>

<p>Import the layout in the script header of a page and use the Layout like
a tag.</p>

        <pre class="code" data-lang="Page"><code>---
import { Layout } from "/layouts/layout.squirrel"
---
<Layout>
    <h1>Title</h1>  // line goes into the hole of layout
    Some text       // line goes into the hole of layout
</Layout>
</code></pre>

</Layout>
